1 Nephi 3:7|And it came to pass that I, Nephi, said unto my father, I will go and do the things which the Lord hath commanded, for I know that he hath not commandments unto the children of men, save he prepare a way for them to do that which he hath commanded them.
Moroni 10:5|5 And by the power of the Holy Spirit you will be able to know the truth of all things.
1 Corinthians 12:30-31|30 Do they all have healing gifts? Do they all speak in tongues? Do they all interpret? 31 Procure, therefore, the best gifts; but I show you a still more excellent way.
Mosiah 2:41|41 And again, I would have you consider the blessed and happy state of those who keep the commandments of God. For behold, they are blessed in all things, both temporal and spiritual; and if they continue faithful to the end, they are received into heaven, that they may dwell with God in a state of endless happiness. O remember, remember that these things are true, for the Lord God has declared it.
Ether 12:4|4 so that those who believe in God may have a firm hope of a better world, yes, even a place at the right hand of God; and this hope comes by faith, provides an anchor to the souls of men, and makes them secure and steadfast, always abounding in good works, being moved to glorify God.
Alma 7:11|11 And he will go forth, suffering pains, afflictions, and temptations of every kind; and this in order that the word may be fulfilled, which says, He will take upon himself the pains and sicknesses of his people.
Alma 32:21|21 And now, as he said concerning faith: Faith is not to have a perfect knowledge of things; so that if you have faith, you have hope in things that are not seen, and that are true.